Scene-FSD (Scene-oriented Fire and Smoke Dataset) is a large-scale dataset constructed from real surveillance systems for fire and smoke detection. It covers four key early-warning scenarios: transportation, open industrial sites, forest monitoring, and high‑rise buildings. All images are sourced from real surveillance scenarios and manually annotated using LabelImg.

This release contains a partial subset of the full dataset. The complete dataset will be made publicly available upon paper acceptance.

